The Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), has flayed the non-compliance of shipping lines to the directive by the Federal Government that all export goods leaving the country should carry Nigerian Export Proceeds (NXP).
    
Chairing a virtual meeting with stakeholders, CBN Governor, Godwin Emefiele, said an audit by the apex bank revealed that several shipping companies were wanting, adding that the non-compliance would attract strict sanctions.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .